title: For Sale:  1200-8400 cut carbines
postcontent:
I have over ten thousand Cut M1 carbines for sale. These weapons were demilled by the US army, Navy and Marines 
During and after the Korean war conflict.I am selling the Carbines in lots of around 1200 Pieces. These include 1200 cut
up barrels, recievers, trigger housings, and assorted other parts. Each lot is guaranteed to have several hundred uncut
complete slide and a very few triggers and sear. There will be over a thousand safeties and Mag catches. I am asking five
thousand dollars a lot, plus I am including a cut up demilled 1917 30 BMG Machine gun.

	A little background, I have bought and sold for over 15 years numerous scrap and junk weapons from numerous armies. 
My Parts originated from Millville New Jersey from a gentleman who had his own firearms company in the sixeties and seventies
These parts have been in cold storage for several decades and some have been stripped for spare parts. I also have over 300 
cut BMG 30 Belt feds and some M2, M3 anm2 50bmg's, plus a warehouse full of spare parts. I only want serious offers, I am
not going to budge from the price. Any serious dealer or collector would be proud to have these parts as there are
many rare variations. some of the variations in these lots are

Recievers of every type, Some not cut!!!
Irwen Pederson, Winchester, Rock-Ola, Standard Products, Inland, IBM, Saginaw s.g., Saginaw S'G', Underwood, QUality and 
Unquality.

Hammer of every type including doglegs and fatboys,

Flip sights of every type,

Barrel bands of every type and Markings.

	Please again only serious offers. 

Terms, Cash on Delivery. WIlling to meet at open places or police stations. Bill of sale and Background check for buyer.

	I will be willing to drive the parts to you within 200 miles as I own a Flatbed. This will add $500 to the cost.
And a final handshake on a deal well done.

	Again only serious offers. I have seven lots, again CASH only!!! No Checks no promises!!! Thank you.

												  James

title: For Sale:  Keltec KSG
postcontent:
The KSG weighs 6.9lbs and is as compact as legally possible with a 26.1" overall length and an 18.5" cylinder bore barrel.  Even with this compact size, the internal dual tube magazines hold an impressive 6 rounds of 12 gage 3" shells each, for a total capacity of 6+6+1 (7 per tube if using 2-3/4" shells).  The simple and reliable pump action feeds from either the left or right tube.  The feed side is manually selected by a lever located behind the trigger guard.  The lever can be positioned in the center detent in order to easily clear the chamber without feeding another round from either magazine.  A cross bolt style safety blocks the sear, and the pump release lever is located in front of the trigger guard.

This KSG is like new. Have original box, papers, sling that came with it.  Been to the range one time. 20 shells fired. $1350 Cash Only. Limited time only. If I find permenant employment before this sells it will no longer be for sale.

profile slide contributes to the balanced center of gravity and compact size of the P7M13.

Made of high-grade steel, the low profile slide keeps the recoiling mass as small as possible. Combined with the optimal grip angle of 110°, the result is a compact, 

accurate, and low recoil pistol well suited to civilian and law enforcement users.

• Polygonal rifling for increased barrel life
• Fluted chamber aids in extraction
• All steel construction

title: For Trade:  Walther P99 AS 40 S&W
postcontent:
P99 AS (Anti Stress) in 40 S&W with 2 12 round magazines, 4 front sight inserts, and 3 different sized backstraps, in original case
Wikipedia clarifies the differences on the AS variant:
This variant comes closest to a traditional Double-Action/Single-Action trigger with a decocker. In Double-Action mode the internal striker is at rest with no pre-load and the trigger travel is 14 mm (0.55 in) long at approximately 38 N (8.5 lbf) trigger pull. When the slide is racked completely to the rear upon (re)loading, the internal striker is manually pre-cocked to Single-Action mode and the trigger remains in the forward position for the first shot and the Anti Stress mode is activated. The trigger travel is 14 mm (0.55 in) long in the Anti Stress mode at approximately 20 N (4.5 lbf) trigger pull. On all subsequent shots, the P99AS is automatically pre-cocked and the trigger travel is reduced to 8 mm (0.3 in) at the same 20 N (4.5 lbf) trigger pull. For manually deactivating the Anti Stress mode and setting the pistol to Double-Action mode the P99AS features a decock key or knob on the slide. The Anti Stress mode can also be manually activated by moving the slide approximately 10 mm (0.4 in) back.[13]
